Vol / Page:  1365
Edition:
Quote:  <i>makomako</i> or <i>mako n</i> -s [Maori] 1 : a New Zealand tree (<i>Aristotelia racemosa</i>) of the family Elaeocarpaceae having a small red berry that turns black at maturity and is used for making wine - called also <i>wineberry 2</i> : the New Zealand bellbird
